</taxonomicName>
species
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="143.[151,1435,1980,2030]" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">
<number box="[151,164,1980,2001]" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" value="1.0">1</number>
. Multilocular disc-pores absent. Posterior stigmatic pore band bifurcated. Cribriform plates in a submedial group of 
<number box="[1367,1403,1980,2001]" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8</number>
on each side of segment IV. Each stigmatic pore band apex with 
<number box="[814,873,2009,2030]" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15</number>
sunken large 
<number box="[1007,1017,2009,2030]" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" value="8.0">8</number>
-shaped pores. (Oriental: Java)..........
